- Create /app/ars.R using a heredoc to avoid quoting issues. The file will contain a modular ARS implementation: helper functions (numeric derivative, validation, hull construction, integration, sampling, log-concavity checks), the main ars() function with input validation and log-concavity checks, and a test() function printing PASS/FAIL messages and writing normal_samples.txt.
- Run Rscript to execute tests.
